      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Before starting the work instruction activity, perform the following steps:</cmd>
            <substeps id="substeps_p24_2ny_xcc" class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Do not begin these tasks without confirmation that personnel directly
                     involved have completed the required training associated with the work
                     instruction activity and have reviewed this document.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Gather necessary tools and equipment as identified below in the Equipment
                     Section.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Wear and use additional Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) and safety
                     equipment required for this specific work instruction.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Obey all applicable safety requirements and procedures.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Notify appropriate personnel of the activity and estimated time needed to
                     complete the tasks.</cmd>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Definition of a Wire Edge:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <p class="- topic/p ">A “Wire Edge” is a circumferential / annular fin of glass at the step down feature that projects
                  vertically from the finish, but does not extend above the top of the sealing
                     surface.<fig id="fig_ynt_wpy_xcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image1.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_nzx_wpy_xcc"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Prerequisite</cmd>
            <substeps id="substeps_t5n_jny_xcc" class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Verify the FTA head is properly maintained and aligned in accordance with
                     Reference Document INS-06-001 FTA Head Verification and Maintenance.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Set up the FTA using Work Instruction INS-03-001 Finish Setup - Soul –
                     FTA.</cmd>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To find the correct step-down location, perform the following steps:</cmd>
            <substeps id="substeps_jgm_lny_xcc" class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Find the specification for the step down height on the drawing that contains
                     the cavity detail information. This is typically the guide ring drawing.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_ank_mny_xcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">If you are not sure where to find the step down height information, the
                           mould shop should be able to provide the correct drawing or
                           information.</li>
                     </ol>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the guide ring drawing, look for the step down specification next to the
                     illustration that details the finish. In the example at right, the step down
                     specification highlighted in yellow is 0.4 mm (0.016 in).</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_djd_4ny_xcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image2.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_yvd_ypy_xcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To set the <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Starting</u> FTA Wire Edge Height, perform the following steps:</cmd>
            <substeps id="substeps_tpx_j4y_xcc" class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Narrow Neck Press and Blow:</b> Set the initial wire edge height to the
                     specification found on the guide ring drawing. For example, if the step down
                     specification is 0.4 mm (0.016 in), set the initial wire edge height to 0.4 mm
                     (0.016 in).</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <note id="note_cpc_m4y_xcc" class="- topic/note ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Refer to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">NNPB</b> Wire Edge Height Chart in the Appendix for
                           example reject ranges.</p>
                     </note>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_jlt_44y_xcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image3.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_zcr_zpy_xcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Press and Blow:</b> Set the initial wire edge height to 70% of the
                     specification found on the guide ring drawing. For example, if the step down
                     specification is 0.4 mm (0.016 in), set the initial wire edge height to 0.28 mm
                     (0.011 in).</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <note id="note_qvf_q4y_xcc" class="- topic/note ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Refer to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Press and Blow</b> Wire Edge Height Chart in the Appendix
                           for example reject ranges.</p>
                     </note>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_ilq_s4y_xcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image4.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_l41_1qy_xcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">
                     <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Blow and Blow</b>:The Blow and Blow process can produce a defect similar
                     to a Wire Edge. Set the initial wire edge height to 0.1 mm (0.004 in).</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <note id="note_z4b_v4y_xcc" class="- topic/note ">
                        <p class="- topic/p ">Refer to the <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Blow and Blow</b> Wire Edge Height Chart in the Appendix
                           for example reject ranges.</p>
                     </note>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_m34_w4y_xcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image5.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_g4k_1qy_xcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">To set the <u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Final</u> FTA Wire Edge Height, perform the following steps: </cmd>
            <substeps id="substeps_czr_y4y_xcc" class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Use the FTA ‘Stop On Trap’ feature to set out the next 10 containers rejected
                     for wire edge / overpress.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_fnh_1py_xcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image6.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_jmb_2qy_xcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Manually inspect the rejected containers that were set out to determine if
                     the containers are true wire edge defects or false rejects.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_ep5_bpy_xcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Determination to be made in consultation with plant quality leaders, and
                           by using one or more of the following methods:<ol id="ol_jgx_cpy_xcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Using GQT-03-154 - Determination of Wire Edge Manual Method
                                 (Needle).</li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Using GQT-03-155 - Determination of Wire Edge - Manual Method
                                 (Fingernail).</li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">Using a magnifier, view the inside edge of the finish for any
                                 sharp glass projecting upward.</li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">An additional Global Quality approved method, as led by plant
                                 quality leaders.</li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_rtg_fpy_xcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image7.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_b32_fqy_xcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Review the FTA trapped images that correspond to each rejected
                     container.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_dxs_gpy_xcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Confirm that the FTA head alignment and light settings are good. </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Confirm that the container was rejected from accurate sealing surface
                           and step-down laser reflections and not stray light or other causes of
                           false rejects.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">If any of the 10 rejected containers are true wire edge defects, save
                           those samples for use as challenge samples.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_u1g_3py_xcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image8.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_a2j_gqy_xcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Based on the results of the manual inspection and in consultation with plant
                     quality leaders, determine if the FTA Wire Edge Height threshold should be
                     increased or decreased based on the following guidelines:</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_nz3_jpy_xcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Confirm there is no cavity correlation of false rejects by checking if
                           the false rejects are from the same cavity or mould. If so, notify the
                           Hot End of the condition.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">If the majority of the 10 rejected containers were "false rejects" –
                           which cannot be rectified at the Hot End – decrease the FTA Wire Edge
                           Height threshold by one unit (one thousands of an inch or two hundredth
                           of a millimeter). For example, if the step down is set to 0.28 mm (0.011
                           in), the Wire Edge Height would be decreased to 0.26 mm or 0.010
                           inches.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">If true wire edge defect samples are available, run those samples to
                           confirm they are still being rejected. If any pass, return to the
                           previous FTA Wire Edge Height threshold.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">Under no circumstances is it acceptable to pass a wire edge sample.</li>
                     </ol>
                     <p class="- topic/p ">
                        <fig id="fig_i4f_3qy_xcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                           <image href="media/image9.jpg"
                                  placement="break"
                                  id="image_pf3_3qy_xcc"
                                  align="center"
                                  class="- topic/image "/>
                        </fig>
                     </p>
                  </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Repeat the process beginning at step 1, using the FTA 'Stop On Trap' feature
                     to set out the next 10 containers rejected for wire edge / overpress.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <ol id="ol_ivf_mpy_xcc" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">On NNPB and Press and Blow containers: Repeat the process until the
                           optimum results are achieved or a maximum <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">of 4 times</b>, whichever
                           comes first.</li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">On Blow and Blow containers: Repeat the process until the optimum
                           results are achieved.</li>
                     </ol>
                  </info>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Upon completion of tasks, perform the following steps:</cmd>
            <substeps id="substeps_y1x_npy_xcc" class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Notify appropriate personnel that the work instruction activity has been
                     completed.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Record and report findings and results.</cmd>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Follow appropriate instructions for notification of findings and results
                     relating to specifications, targets and/or reaction limits.</cmd>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
         </step>
      </steps>
